  "benefit_assessment_plain_language": "M5f still does not make the toy-hifi read-alignment batch faster. Its CUDA-side benefit is coverage and scheduler correctness: cuFlye now accepts an explicit heterogeneous real fixture list, groups 68 real reads into 4 supported CUDA shape groups, runs packed CPU/CUDA batches per group, and preserves every per-read oracle diff. The batch is still only 141 input records and four CUDA launches, so launch/copy/setup overhead dominates; the next ROI target is larger non-toy batches or a persistent grouped worker.",
